sentences: Chaim "Efim" Schachmeister (22 July 1894 – 6 October 1944) was a German violinist and bandleader.
Born in Kiev to Romanian Jewish parents, from 1910 to 1913 he studied music at the Stern Conservatory in Berlin.
In 1915 he joined the Popescu Gypsy Band (Zigeuner-Kapelle Popescu).
In 1923 he became bandleader, and the following year embarked on a German tour that ended in April 1925 with an engagement at the Hotel Excelsior in Berlin.

"Schachmeister's style evolved over the course of the 1920s from ragtime to the more modern jazz.
His 1927 recording of "Saint Louis Blues" is illustrative of his tendency to combine elements of Blues and the shtetl style.
He died in Argentina in 1944, aged fifty.
